==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Divining
<hw>Di*vin"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>That divines; for
divining.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Divining rod</b></col>, <cd>a rod, commonly of witch
hazel, with forked branches, used by those who claim to be able to
discover water or metals under ground by sensing them through such a
rod.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diviningly</ent>⟦br⟧
